              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:04201104100018} καθαρός may be rendered in some languages as ‘pure in the eyes of God’ or even ‘right in the eyes of God.’|In a number of languages there is simply no relationship between physical cleanness and ritual acceptability or purity. Accordingly, it may be necessary to render καθαρός in {S:04201104100018} and similar contexts as ‘acceptable to God’ or ‘good in God’s eyes’ or ‘good as God thinks.’</Comments>
